eling can be extended to provide a comprehensive view of prevention and deterrence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aCaplan, Joel M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPiza, Eric L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520968349?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968349423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968349/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles